<span id="Description"></span>
==Beschreibung==

The [[Image:Draft_AddNamedGroup.svg|24px]] '''Draft AddNamedGroup''' command creates a named [[Std_Group|Std Group]] and moves selected objects to that group.

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Anwendung==

# Optionally select one or more objects.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Draft_AddNamedGroup.svg|16px]] [[Draft_AddNamedGroup|Add a new named group]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Utilities → [[Image:Draft_AddNamedGroup.svg|16px]] Add a new named group}} option from the menu, or from the [[Tree_view|Tree view]] or [[3D_view|3D view]] context menu.
# The {{MenuCommand|Add group}} task panel opens.
# Enter a {{MenuCommand|Group name}}.
# Press the {{Button|OK}} button.

<span id="Notes"></span>
==Hinweise==

* For more information about organizing your model see [[Document_structure|Document structure]] and [[Arch_tutorial#Organizing_your_model|Arch tutorial]].


